cs.GT, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.CE, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper extensively uses auction theory to model the interactions between customers, CCN managers, and private cloud providers. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper deals with cloud computing and resource allocation, which falls under the purview of distributed computing. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses cloud of clouds networks (CCNs) and the interactions between CCN managers and private cloud providers, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes a comprehensive framework for resource gathering and allocation in cloud computing, which involves computational methods and techniques. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the design and implementation of an options-based sequential auction (OBSA) for the first stage of resource allocation, which involves software engineering principles.
